{
  "type": "feature",
  "title": "Quick Numbers & Dates Dictation drill (listening micro-card on Home)",
  "description": "Add a new 'Quick Numbers & Dates' listening micro-drill accessible from the Home page, alongside existing quick cards (Quick Speak, Quick Grammar, Quick Conversation, Voicemail Drill, Connected Speech Drill, etc.). Real-world listening frequently breaks down on numbers (years, prices, phone numbers, times, dates, large quantities) ‚Äî a focused dictation drill addresses this gap.\n\nBackend (app/routers/listening.py): add endpoint POST /api/listening/numbers-drill that returns a JSON payload of 5 items, each: {id, kind: 'price'|'year'|'phone'|'time'|'date'|'quantity', spoken_text (the natural English to speak, e.g. 'It costs three hundred forty-nine dollars and ninety-nine cents'), expected_answer (canonical normalized string, e.g. '$349.99'), accept_variants (list of acceptable normalized strings, e.g. ['349.99','$349.99','349 dollars 99 cents']), hint}. Generate via copilot_client using a new prompt in app/prompts.py (NUMBERS_DRILL_PROMPT) that instructs the LLM to produce varied difficulty items in strict JSON. Add POST /api/listening/numbers-drill/submit that records attempts and returns per-item correctness using normalize+compare logic (strip spaces, $, commas, dashes; lowercase). Persist results in a new mini table:\n\nSCHEMA addition + migration (database.py both SCHEMA and _MIGRATIONS):\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS numbers_drill_attempts (id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT, kind TEXT NOT NULL, expected TEXT NOT NULL, user_answer TEXT, is_correct INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0, created_at TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now')));\nMigration entry: ('20250XXX_numbers_drill_attempts', \"CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS numbers_drill_attempts (id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT, kind TEXT NOT NULL, expected TEXT NOT NULL, user_answer TEXT, is_correct INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0, created_at TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now')))\"). Since this is a new table, CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS is sufficient (no ALTER needed).\n\nFrontend: add a card on Home.tsx 'Quick Numbers & Dates' that opens a lightweight inline panel (or new route /numbers-drill component) which: fetches 5 items, uses window.speechSynthesis to speak each spoken_text (sanitized, configurable rate 0.9), shows a text input for the user to type what they heard, a 'Replay' button, a 'Slow' toggle (rate 0.6), and after submit shows per-item correct/incorrect with the expected normalized form. Display a small summary (e.g., 4/5) and a 'Try another set' button. Include dark-mode styles consistent with existing quick cards.\n\nTests: unit test for the normalization/compare helper (tests/unit/), and an API integration test that mocks copilot_client to return a fixed JSON list and asserts /numbers-drill returns 5 items and /submit records attempts with correct is_correct flags.\n\nFiles to modify (‚â§5): app/routers/listening.py, app/prompts.py, app/database.py, frontend/src/pages/Home.tsx, frontend/src/api.ts (and a small new component co-located in Home or pages ‚Äî count as part of Home edit).",
